============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the Renaissance?
A1: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q2: What is relativity?
A2: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

Q3: What is machine learning?
A3: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

Q4: What is the periodic table?
A4: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

Q5: What is a black hole?
A5: A black hole is a region where gravity is so strong
     that nothing, not even light, can escape. Formed from
     collapsed massive stars. Event horizon is the point of
     no return.

